#. type: Title ===
#: _posts/2022-02-22-quarkus-superheroes-to-the-rescue.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Villain Service"
msgstr "Servicio de villanos"

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-02-22-quarkus-superheroes-to-the-rescue.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Villain service is a blocking HTTP microservice exposing CRUD operations on a `+Villain+` data model. In fact, the `+Villain+` data model is identical to the `+Hero+` data model in the <<hero-service,Hero service>> (other than the table's name). It also implements all the same use cases as the Hero service. The only difference is that the Villain service is blocking, and it uses the https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache#solution-1-using-the-active-record-pattern[active record pattern^] from https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache[Quarkus Hibernate ORM with Panache^]."
msgstr "El servicio Villain es un microservicio HTTP bloqueante que expone operaciones CRUD en un modelo de datos `Villain`. De hecho, el modelo de datos `Villain` es idéntico al modelo de datos `Hero` del servicio  link:#hero-service[Hero] (aparte del nombre de la tabla). También implementa los mismos casos de uso que el servicio Hero. La única diferencia es que el servicio Villain es bloqueante, y utiliza el  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache#solution-1-using-the-active-record-pattern[patrón de registro activo, window=_blank] de  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache[Quarkus Hibernate ORM con Panache, window=_blank]."

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2022-02-22-quarkus-superheroes-to-the-rescue.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The REST layer is implemented using https://quarkus.io/guides/resteasy-reactive[RESTEasy Reactive^] with blocking endpoints. Data is persisted into a https://www.postgresql.org[PostgreSQL^] database. The Villain service also creates some custom configurations which show how to use https://quarkus.io/guides/config-mappings[`+ConfigMapping+`^] objects. Additionally, the Villain service favors https://quarkus.io/guides/cdi-reference#qualified-injected-fields[field injection^] of beans over https://quarkus.io/guides/cdi-reference#simplified-constructor-injection[constructor injection^]. The Villain service contains a full suite of unit and integration tests, using https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-testing#further-simplification-with-injectmock[mocking^], https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-testing#using-spies-instead-of-mocks-with-injectspy[spying^], and testing within https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-testing#tests-and-transactions[isolated transactions^]."
msgstr "La capa REST se implementa utilizando  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/resteasy-reactive[RESTEasy Reactive, window=_blank] con puntos finales de bloqueo. Los datos se persisten en una base de datos  link:https://www.postgresql.org[PostgreSQL, window=_blank]. El servicio Villain también crea algunas configuraciones personalizadas que muestran cómo utilizar  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/config-mappings[`ConfigMapping`, window=_blank] objetos. Además, el servicio Villain favorece la  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/cdi-reference#qualified-injected-fields[inyección de campos, window=_blank] de los beans sobre  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/cdi-reference#simplified-constructor-injection[la inyección de constructores, window=_blank]. El servicio Villain contiene un conjunto completo de pruebas unitarias y de integración, utilizando  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-testing#further-simplification-with-injectmock[mocking, window=_blank],  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-testing#using-spies-instead-of-mocks-with-injectspy[spying, window=_blank] y pruebas dentro de  link:https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-testing#tests-and-transactions[transacciones aisladas, window=_blank]."

#. type: delimited block =
#: _posts/2022-02-22-quarkus-superheroes-to-the-rescue.adoc
#, fuzzy
